The tone of the two (genuine) extant books of his elegies confirms the impression of his character which we derive from the language of Horace. He appears as a gentle, tender, somewhat melancholy soul, marked more by genuineness of natural feeling than by learning or force of expression. Od. 1. 33 18 also addressed to him. The date of the Epistle cannot be precisely determined, but it may be safely placed within the limits assigned to the Epistles generally, 24- 20 Β. c.
